CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 6, 1957, pg. 16 reads: "7. Thousands jammed the Meadow Gold Dairies booth for samples of ice cream. Attending, left to right, Miss Sherlynn Dudley, Mrs. Beatrice Cook, Miss Viviane Swain and A. J. Marmo."
TitMainTitle: Three women, including Sherlynn Dudley,  Beatrice Cook, and Viviane Swain, standing with A. J. Marmo in Meadow Gold booth, in Syria Mosque for the 1957 Pittsburgh Courier Homes Service Fair
